  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing Hero Section Prototype**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the initial prototype of this hero section. I\'m building it with React, utilizing Tailwind CSS for styling, and incorporating the Lucide React icons as requested. The Inter font from Google Fonts is also integrated. I\'m aiming for a basic, functional layout at this stage, before further refinements.\n\n\n**Constructing Hero Design Components**\n\nI\'m now implementing the detailed design elements for the hero section. I\'ve integrated a full-height, non-scrolling design with a background video. The blur overlay with a CSS mask has been added, and I\'m adding the liquid glass effect. I\'m also including the animation for the blur fade-up effect. I\'ve designed the navbar with elements that are conditionally visible across the break points, and the mobile menu is in progress.\n\n\n**Defining Hero Section Layout**\n\nI\'m now outlining the layout of the hero section. On the left, I\'m integrating metadata (Star, Clock, Calendar), the title, description, and CTA buttons (Watch Now, Learn More). On the right, I\'ll place the navigation arrow buttons (Previous, Next). I\'m also planning the stagger delays for the animation. I\'m using sm and lg breakpoints for responsiveness. The next step is to modify `index.css` to add custom styles, considering Tailwind v4\'s structure with `@theme`. I\'ll update `Landing.tsx` to integrate these layout components and animations.\n\n\n**Implementing Liquid Glass Effects**\n\nI\'m now incorporating liquid glass styling and blur fade-up animations. I\'ve focused on styling the `liquid-glass` class with a translucent background, blur effects, and subtle shadowing. A gradient is used within a pseudo-element for the liquid glass effect, and I\'ve also implemented the blurFadeUp animation. I\'m applying these styles to the hero section.\n\n\n**Refactoring Hero Section Logic**\n\nI\'m now overhauling `Landing.tsx`. I\'ve outlined the core components: a video background, mask blur overlay, navbar, mobile menu overlay, and hero content. I\'ve imported the necessary icons from `lucide-react`, now structuring the layout with state for the mobile menu. I\'m developing the navigation with a list of links.\n\n\n**Integrating Video Background**\n\nI\'m now integrating the background video and blur overlay. I\'ve placed the video as a fixed, full-screen background using Tailwind classes. I\'m adding a bottom blur overlay with a mask to create a visual effect, but I need to ensure it\'s responsive. I\'ve added a content wrapper and started the navbar, focusing on its responsive design.\n\n\n**Adding Navigation Animation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on navigation animation for both desktop and mobile views. I\'m adding `animate-blur-fade-up` with varying delays. I\'m also ensuring the mobile menu is responsive. I\'m adding liquid glass styling. I\'m using Tailwind classes for responsiveness.\n\n\n\n**Refining Menu Interactions**\n\nI\'m now refining the mobile menu toggle. I\'ve focused on ensuring smooth animations for the menu icon using `rotate` and `scale` transformations with transition timing. I\'m leveraging the `z-50` index to keep it on top. I\'m also addressing the state change for the menu\'s visibility and responsiveness using inline styling for animation delays. I\'ve finished implementing the search and user buttons, with liquid glass effects.\n\n\n**Finalizing Mobile Menu Animations**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on the mobile menu animations, ensuring they\'re responsive and perform smoothly. I\'ve integrated a keyframe animation with scale, rotate and translate. I\'m focusing on the animation of the X icon, which is now functioning correctly. I\'m also ensuring the menu\'s state toggles are correctly set, with transitions.\n\n\n**Enhancing Menu Link Animations**\n\nI\'m now refining the animation on menu links. I\'m focusing on the responsive styling for transitions. I\'ve integrated `transitionDelay` using `isMobileMenuOpen` state, ensuring smooth transitions. I\'m also addressing transforms and opacity. I\'m finalizing the responsiveness using inline styles. I\'m also ensuring the visibility and responsiveness of the search and user buttons, with liquid glass effects.\n\n\n**Optimizing Layout Responsiveness**\n\nI\'m now focusing on optimizing responsiveness, especially the layout. I\'m reviewing the breakpoints and spacing across different screen sizes for consistency, implementing fluid typography and responsive image sizing. I am making use of Tailwind\'s responsive modifiers to adjust padding, margins, and font sizes.\n\n\n**Refining Section Content**\n\nI\'m now refining the section content, focusing on the metadata, title, description, and CTA buttons. I\'ve integrated `Star`, `Clock`, and `Calendar` icons to the metadata, then styled the title, description, and buttons. I\'m adding `animate-blur-fade-up` with staggered delays for each element. The design, including responsiveness, is almost complete.\n\n\n**Adjusting Call-to-Action Buttons**\n\nI\'m now adjusting the call-to-action buttons. I\'ve designed and styled the buttons (\"Watch Now\", \"Learn More\") with a focus on visual appeal, animation, and responsive design, integrating them within a flex container. I\'m adding `animate-blur-fade-up` with staggered delays. I\'m also addressing the responsiveness of these buttons across different screen sizes.\n\n\n**Addressing Navigation Arrows**\n\nI\'m now checking the responsiveness of the navigation arrows, adjusting their positioning with Tailwind\'s classes. I\'m focusing on ensuring the top offset of the right arrow remains consistent on desktop and mobile. I\'m also reviewing `mask-image` usage to address a potential compatibility issue with WebKit browsers, having used inline styles to resolve the issue.\n\n\n**Updating Font & Styles**\n\nI\'m now changing the default font in `index.css` to `Inter` and integrating liquid glass and animation styles. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and visual enhancements. After this change I\'ll replace `Landing.tsx` with updated layout.\n\n\n**Implementing Global Styles**\n\nI\'m now changing the global styles by creating a new `index.css` file. I\'m importing the `Inter` font directly and setting it as the default font. I\'ve also added the liquid glass effect, globally and updated colors. I\'ve also set a black background and white text for better contrast.\n\n\n**Refining Glass Effect Implementation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the liquid glass effect, implementing the provided CSS styles for the `.liquid-glass` class. I\'ve successfully set up the blur and gradient overlay within this class, and the liquid glass styling should now be correctly applied to elements across the layout. I\'m also ensuring the mask is correctly applied.\n\n\n**Finalizing Element Animations**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on element animations. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and fluid transitions with staggered effects. The title, description, and CTA buttons have been styled with `animate-blur-fade-up`, with appropriate delays. I\'m refining the menu link animations and ensuring smooth transitions, responsiveness, and appropriate timing.\n\n\n**Finalizing Blur Overlay**\n\nI\'m now completing the blur overlay. I\'m focusing on responsiveness with inline styles for the mask gradient. I\'ve integrated `linear-gradient(to top, black 0%, transparent 45%)` to enhance the visual effect. I\'ve also incorporated vendor prefixes for broader compatibility, addressing WebKit browsers.\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Hero Implementation**\n\nI\'m now integrating the mobile menu interactions within the hero section, specifically addressing visibility and event handling. I\'m ensuring all components, including the menu icon, search, and user buttons, respond correctly to clicks and state changes. I\'ve focused on ensuring the `Landing.tsx` integration with other components works correctly. I am also working on `link.delay` values. I am updating responsiveness.\n\n\n**Refining Animations and Links**\n\nI\'m now refining the animation and responsiveness of mobile links, using a staggered animation with `transition-delay`. I\'m working with transforms and opacity to create smooth transitions. I am finishing the visual enhancements by making sure the search and user buttons are responsive and have liquid glass effects.\n\n\n**Finalizing Responsive Layout**\n\nI\'m now integrating responsive styling for all components within the layout, particularly the mobile menu, ensuring seamless transitions and consistent behavior across devices. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and fluid transitions with staggered effects. I\'m checking the menu visibility and event handling, with correct integration of all components. I am adjusting the CSS and ensuring all `link.delay` values.\n\n\n**Adjusting Responsive Interactions**\n\nI\'m now integrating responsive styling for the search and user button interaction within the mobile menu, ensuring the interaction is seamless on all devices. I\'m focusing on responsiveness and fluid transitions with the menu. I\'m checking the menu visibility and adjusting event handling to finalize the component integration. I\'ve successfully adjusted the CSS, now all `link.delay` values.\n\n\n**Refining Section Metadata**\n\nI\'m now refining the section metadata for improved visual presentation and responsiveness. I\'ve focused on styling the metadata with Tailwind classes for responsiveness. I\'m adding `animate-blur-fade-up` with a 300ms delay. The `Star`, `Clock`, and `Calendar` icons have been styled and integrated within the metadata, improving readability and visual appeal. I\'m finishing the metadata styles.\n\n\n**Finalizing Hero Content**\n\nI\'m now putting the finishing touches on the hero content, ensuring responsiveness and visual appeal. I\'ve successfully styled the title with the staggered fade-up animation. I\'ve also incorporated the description and call-to-action buttons. Responsiveness is now finalized and the visual presentation is complete.\n\n\n**Adjusting Animation Delays**\n\nI\'m now refining the animation delays for the call-to-action buttons and navigation arrows, ensuring they are staggered appropriately for a smooth visual flow. The buttons and arrows are responsive across screen sizes, with a focus on a staggered fade-up. I\'m adding `animate-blur-fade-up` and adjusting delays for each.\n\n\n"
