    modified_response: "I have implemented the cinematic scroll-scrubbing animation using the 120 frames you uploaded. \n\nHere is what was completed:\n- **Frame Pipeline**: The raw 120 PNG frames were collected and securely moved to the static `public/frames` distribution directory.\n- **Scroll Engine**: I implemented a custom `<HeroScrub />` canvas renderer using Framer Motion\'s `useScroll` and `useTransform`. This creates a buttery-smooth, hardware-accelerated scrubbing experience tied directly to the user\'s scroll position.\n- **Architectural Adjustment**: The hero viewport was upgraded with sticky positioning spanning `250vh`. This ensures the cinematic animation finishes its sequence precisely before the seamless restaurant menu transitions into view.\n- **Object-Cover Rendering**: The canvas automatically calculates viewport boundaries and applies an intelligent `object-cover` crop dynamically, perfectly maintaining the ratio regardless of device resizing.\n\nWhen you scroll down, it will physically scrub the video frames before seamlessly leading into the beautiful food descriptions."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
